{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/appendicitis/background-information/causes/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"2124e989-ba40-5b9e-a486-850a63b3a842","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field d0cc3e96-2e82-4538-8b38-5aa1353b7a25 --><h2>What causes it?</h2><!-- end field d0cc3e96-2e82-4538-8b38-5aa1353b7a25 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 39006d7d-43f8-4734-a8a1-b284b5092882 --><!-- begin field 4f2c1c05-091c-4629-9802-43a3dfd6fb3a --><p><strong>The aetiology and pathogenesis of acute appendicitis remain largely unknown, but it is thought to be caused by luminal obstruction in about 50% of cases </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Gorter, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Rentea, 2017</a>]<strong>.</strong></p><ul><li>The main causes of luminal obstruction are thought to be faecolith (hard mass of faecal matter), lymphoid hyperplasia during an infection, impacted stool, foreign body, or rarely appendiceal or caecal tumour [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Bhangu, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Baird, 2017</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Rentea, 2017</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Howell, 2018</a>]. There may be underlying:<ul><li>Genetic factors — a positive family history is associated with a nearly three-fold increased risk of appendicitis [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Rentea, 2017</a>].</li><li>Environmental factors — there is a typically seasonal presentation with peaks in the summer months [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Bhangu, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Rentea, 2017</a>].</li><li>Infection — usually with aerobic and anaerobic bacteria, such as <em>Escherichia coli</em> and<em> Bacteroides</em> spp. [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Bhangu, 2015</a>].</li><li>Malignancy (rare) — in about 1% of people with appendicitis there may be an underlying neuroendocrine tumour of the appendix (carcinoid), adenocarcinoma, or mucinous cystadenoma [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Bhangu, 2015</a>].</li></ul></li><li>Luminal obstruction leads to distension of the appendix owing to increased mucus production, bacterial overgrowth, and suppurative inflammation. This results in impaired lymphatic and venous drainage from the appendix, with eventual ischaemia and necrosis, and potential perforation [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Stringer, 2017</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Howell, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/appendicitis/references/\">Synder, 2018</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 4f2c1c05-091c-4629-9802-43a3dfd6fb3a --><!-- end item 39006d7d-43f8-4734-a8a1-b284b5092882 -->","topic":{"id":"34a7018e-bdb2-5fb9-8f39-14b87cb77872","topicId":"38888cc0-af2f-4224-93a9-2ffe35d3793c","topicName":"Appendicitis","slug":"appendicitis","lastRevised":"Last revised in July 2020","chapters":[{"id":"c3867ccc-2088-5ea2-a8b8-c8a8fa3b1495","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"cadf0862-729f-56ee-b5c8-c92c5a72cbb5","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"efd5c1ac-3b3a-5b2c-82d5-19cda81e37fe","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"5c0768a7-4653-5b13-9bdd-b0696c5ea29a","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"1c4d3384-d57f-500b-ac6c-5360cef5f665","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"665f1a5d-97d4-56f8-a6d9-9fccc1bb162b","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"2b7bc994-71ff-5c70-9d2d-e88756d8ebeb","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"6546ce13-0da8-59ad-8062-384d7dc545ec","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"8fd8907b-64f5-5949-a722-c92fde97c4e7","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"4094c54b-d832-5e5d-893b-0ee5418989a6","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"0cacff5e-d8d9-5053-b381-6f678b14f8c0","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"99de95cd-a3de-5bb5-a658-8a7a495f55fd","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"510fb9da-0f73-516f-9d6e-cda2f09a6ec1","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"bd0bf4d1-012c-5b82-a8a7-992e85eea281","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"2124e989-ba40-5b9e-a486-850a63b3a842","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"8967b141-4534-5554-8baf-8eee87d04eaf","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"949c28c0-203f-5e3d-9504-b0e2b0c140cc","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"},{"id":"557c4557-3b35-5ec3-9537-b07e3c9c6258","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"}]},{"id":"7b07935e-848b-54ec-8132-0cc2066ad303","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"2e327864-e521-54a4-a7f6-1e32f581cc0a","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},{"id":"8cbf80b6-7f36-5f3f-a3